node.text: Jessica Alba built her wildly successful Honest Company from the ground up — but not everyone had confidence that the actress and businesswoman could achieve her dream. In one of this week's cover stories, Alba opens up to PEOPLE about how she combated naysayers who didn't believe she could run a prosperous company. 🙏 "No one believed I could do it in the first place," she says. "If you're doing something that you haven't done, or has never been done before, what do you really have to lose?" ❤️ Pick up the issue on stands Friday, and tap the bio link for more. | 📷: @mrmikerosenthal
